#1 Copy the test to Clipboard:

Object Name: VU_copyToClipboard

Rule Inputs:
1. textToCopy (Text)

Code: 
a!richTextDisplayField(
  labelPosition: "COLLAPSED",
  value: a!richTextItem(
    text: "Click here to copy",
    link: 'type!{http://www.appian.com/ae/types/2009}CopyToClipboardLink'(textToCopy: ri!textToCopy)
  )
)

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

#2 Try Function:

The try() function can allow you to get some error handling within Appian, although it will not work to catch all error types.

Code:
try(concat(), fn!lastError().details)

Output:
Expression evaluation error at function 'concat': Too few parameters for function; expected at least 1 parameters, but found 0 parameters.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

#3 Eval Function:

Converts the text to SAIL code, then evaluates the code, similar to eval() in JavaScript.

Code:
eval("len(""Navin"")")

Output:
5

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

#4 Enum Function

The enum() is similar to enumerate().

Code:
enum(5)

Output:
{1, 2, 3, 4, 5}

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

#5 Sort Function:

Code 1:
sort({4,3,2,1})

Output:
{1,2,3,4}

Code 2:
sort({"Z", "A","D"})

Output:
{"A", "D", "Z"}
